Wash and dry all produce. Place @jasmine rice{1%unit} in a #fine-mesh sieve{} and
rinse until water runs clear. Place in a #small pot{} with @water{1%cup} and
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to a low simmer.
Cook until rice is tender, about ~{15%minutes} (we'll start the steak then).
Keep covered off heat for at least ~{10%minutes}, or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and finely chop @garlic{3%cloves} until you have about 1 TBSP.
Place @diced steak{1%unit} in a #medium bowl{} and pat dry with #paper towels{}.
Toss with @Kikkoman® traditionally brewed soy sauce{2%units}, half the garlic,
@sugar{1%tsp}, @pepper{} and a large pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to marinate.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{1%unit}, @sriracha{1%unit},
@water{1%tsp}, and as much remaining garlic as you'd like. Season with @salt{}.

Peel and grate @carrots{3%ounce} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.
Halve @Persian cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise
into half-moons. In a small bowl, combine cucumber, @white wine vinegar{1%unit},
@sugar{½%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to quick-pickle.

Once rice is done, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{}
over high heat. Once oil is shimmering, add steak (leaving any excess
marinade in bowl) and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, about ~{3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Divide rice between
bowls and top with steak, grated carrot, pickled cucumber, and sriracha mayo.

> Bowlify - To transform (see: deconstruct) an iconic dish into a multi-layered
> masterpiece, typically assembled in a round eating vessel. We beefed up
> this bowl with tender pieces of steak after a quick-marinade in soy and
> garlic, seared and piled atop steamy rice along with shredded carrot,
> pickled cucumber, and a drizzle of sriracha mayo. We know this'll be right
> up your alley.

-- Increase @water{2%cups} and @sugar{2%tsp} for 4 servings.